@node Architecture
@chapter Architecture
@cindex architecture
@cindex AgentCore
@cindex component diagram

This chapter describes Codebud's internal structure: what each component
does, how data flows between them, and why the boundaries are drawn where
they are.

@menu
* Component Overview::          The six subsystems and their roles.
* The Agent Loop::              Data flow through a single request.
* AgentCore::                   The central orchestrator.
* LLMPlanner::                  Prompt construction and JSON parsing.
* SafetyEngine::                Two-layer validation.
* Executor::                    Step-by-step execution.
* Sandbox::                     Controlled command execution.
* MemoryStore::                 Persistent timeline.
* ToolRegistry::                Tool catalogue.
* LLM Stub::                    Backend-agnostic LLM interface.
* File Layout::                 Where everything lives on disk.
@end menu


